LeetCode 121. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock
Problem

You are given an array prices where:

prices[i] = stock price on day i

Choose:

One day to buy
One future day to sell

Return the maximum profit.

If no profit is possible, return 0.

Example
prices = [7,1,5,3,6,4]

Buy at 1
Sell at 6

Profit = 6 - 1 = 5
1. Brute Force
Idea

Try every possible pair (buy, sell).

Compute:

profit = prices[j] - prices[i]

where:

j > i

Keep maximum profit.

Time Complexity
O(n²)
Space Complexity
O(1)

Code
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {

        int maxProfit = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < prices.length; i++) {

            for (int j = i + 1; j < prices.length; j++) {

                maxProfit = Math.max(
                    maxProfit,
                    prices[j] - prices[i]
                );
            }
        }

        return maxProfit;
    }
}

2. Prefix Minimum Array
Idea

For each day:

profit =
currentPrice - minimumPriceSeenBefore

First compute:

minPrice[i]
=
minimum stock price from day 0 to day i

Then:

profit = prices[i] - minPrice[i]
Example
prices = [7,1,5,3,6,4]

minPrice =
[7,1,1,1,1,1]

profit =
[0,0,4,2,5,3]

Answer = 5
Time Complexity
O(n)
Space Complexity
O(n)

Code
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {

        int n = prices.length;

        int[] minPrice = new int[n];

        minPrice[0] = prices[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            minPrice[i] = Math.min(
                minPrice[i - 1],
                prices[i]
            );
        }

        int maxProfit = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            maxProfit = Math.max(
                maxProfit,
                prices[i] - minPrice[i]
            );
        }

        return maxProfit;
    }
}

3. Optimal (Running Minimum)
Key Observation

We don't need the entire prefix array.

We only need:

minimum stock price seen so far

At each day:

profit =
currentPrice - minPrice

Update answer.

Then update:

minPrice = min(minPrice, currentPrice)
Algorithm
Initialize:
minPrice = prices[0]
maxProfit = 0
Traverse array
Calculate profit
Update answer
Update minimum price
Time Complexity
O(n)
Space Complexity
O(1)

Code (Optimal)
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {

        int minPrice = prices[0];
        int maxProfit = 0;

        for (int price : prices) {

            maxProfit = Math.max(
                maxProfit,
                price - minPrice
            );

            minPrice = Math.min(
                minPrice,
                price
            );
        }

        return maxProfit;
    }
}

Kadane's Algorithm Interpretation

This problem can also be viewed as a Kadane variant.

Convert prices into daily differences:

prices = [7,1,5,3,6,4]

diff =
[-6, +4, -2, +3, -2]

Now find the maximum subarray sum on diff.

The maximum subarray sum equals the maximum profit.

Kadane Solution
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {

        int currSum = 0;
        int maxProfit = 0;

        for (int i = 1; i < prices.length; i++) {

            int diff = prices[i] - prices[i - 1];

            currSum = Math.max(0, currSum + diff);

            maxProfit = Math.max(maxProfit, currSum);
        }

        return maxProfit;
    }
}

